
This example checks whether the background DM halo contributes
to the particle tidal tensor. Dark matter and star particles are 
placed in an external Hernquist halo and evolved for one step 
without self-gravity.  

(Hernquist IC profile paramters:
  total mass M: 1.99e12  [Msun]
  characterstic radius a: 52.19    [kpc]
  particle resolution mres: 1.42e6 [Msun]
)

configure with:

./configure --with-kernel=wendland-C2 --enable-gravitational-tidal-tensors=yes --with-ext-potential=hernquist

Then run run.sh